During the Final Business Review Business Process, the Product Owner makes sure that everything is as it should be regarding the new Release. The Product Owner does the following checks:

. The develop and master branches should contain the correct versions of the release. (not the rc version or any other version).
. The GitHub pre-release flag should be unchecked.
. The README files of the Release should be correct, and all links should be working.
. The public documentation website (including all relevant files) should also contain the correct versions of the release (not the rc version or any other version).



In the Announce the release of the stable version the Product Owner announces the release of the stable version to the community.
